    const int i00 = blockIdx.x*blockDim.x + threadIdx.x;
```

But then we run into issues for `i01 >= 65536`. So the solution is to just swap `blockIdx.x` and `blockIdx.y` but without touching `blockdim` and `threadIdx` (since they are conceptually different).

